Motshabi Jacob (64) went missing on 15 December 2017. Photo: Supplied Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories The police in Kagisho have opened a missing person investigation following the disappearance of an elderly resident, Motshabi Jacob (64). Jacob’s family reported him missing on 12 January. He was last seen on 15 December 2017. The police description states that he is tall, slender and dark in complexion, with black and grey hair. Anyone with in­formation that might help to reunite Jacob with his family is urged to call the investigating officer, Sgt Tiny Segami of the Kagisho police, on 082-736-8908. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  